Well...it is a combination of the two: who's there first and who engaged first. I doubt, however, that VI or anyone would hold it against me for bowing out either. You want to cling to extremes in personalities as a way to legitimize the list (from asshole to angel), but the actions of those who abuse courtesy fails to establish why asshole and angel alike should discard their practices and abide by it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/ubelhaven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belhaven</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Froglok Dar Knight</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(8/12/02 10:40:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=465.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire List</span><hr size=1> Ah - I knew this was coming.  I happened to be present in the epiccamp chat when Yinta stopped by.<br>
<br>
There are a fixed number of spawns for Ragefire in any given period.  In order to have a reasonable chance of getting one, you need to be present in the zone when he pops, or you'll lose it to someone who IS present, as they know to mobilize before you do.<br>
<br>
Given that his spawn cycle can be up to 6 days, you need to be able to devote at least 6 days, but potentially more if a patch occurs near the end of the cycle.  <br>
<br>
Now, I, like many other EQ players, work for a living.  I need some advance planning to arrange to be away from work a week.  The delays inherent to the list work in my favor.  Am I happy that I'm up next march?  Not really - but now I can plan for the event as the time gets closers.<br>
<br>
--------<br>
To claim that there is no way for folks to know about the list is fallacious.  When a cleric is ready for the Skyfire camp, they go to Skyfire.  There, they find the sitting clerics who tell them “there is a list”.<br>
<br>
Have you ever gone to a zone and wanted to camp a mob to find the camp taken by others?  They tell you “You can join, but there is a list of people that have already asked to join.  You’ll be added to that list”. Do you object to the list, and form your own camp?  Probably not.<br>
<br>
What Yinta and some of the others are apparently objecting to is the SIZE of the list, not the list in itself.   Sorry – Verant determined that size.<br>
<br>
There is no way to prevent another cleric from coming to the site and setting up camp.  And, in fact, Verant’s rules explicitly allow it.  What the folks who subscribe to the list are saying is “Don’t bother”.  The list supporters believe they can mobilize a sufficient force to kill Ragefire before you can, so your time will be wasted.<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
Originally, Yinta had suggested an alternative which involved using a RANDOM to determine which order Clerics would go in, with a rerandom occasionally to account for newcomers.    Other flaws aside, system has the potential for a cleric to NEVER be allowed to camp it... which I think is the fatal flaw.<br>
 <p>Belhaven<BR>
